+- Verified: pass — Zero console errors on all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak). Clean start correctly gives no penalty. Early accel correctly detected and penalty applied. Turn speed loss confirmed (straight: 53, turning: 57 — less increase than pure accel). Surface blend stays at 0.000 on road for all karts.
+
+## Iteration 15 — Focus: Visual & Audio Polish
+- **Engine sound smoothing (lowpass filter + fade-out)**: Added a `BiquadFilterNode` (lowpass) between the engine sawtooth oscillator and gain node. Cutoff frequency modulates with speed (400Hz at idle → 1200Hz at top speed), making the engine sound warm at low RPM and brighter at high RPM instead of a harsh raw sawtooth. On startup, gain ramps from 0.001 over 50ms to prevent the initial click. On `stopEngine()`, gain fades to 0.0001 over 50ms before the oscillator is stopped and disconnected via `setTimeout`, eliminating the audible pop from abrupt disconnection.
+- **Dynamic shadow camera following player**: The directional light (and its shadow camera) now tracks the player kart's position every visual frame. Previously the light was fixed at (50,80,30) with ±60 shadow bounds — shadows disappeared once the player moved ~60 units from origin. Now the light position updates to `(playerX+50, playerY+80, playerZ+30)` with the target centered on the player. Also added `directionalLight.target` to the scene graph in scene.js so `updateMatrixWorld` propagates correctly.
+- **Hook missing audio events (drift, boost, collision)**: Connected 5 audio functions that were implemented in audio.js but never called: `playDriftStart()` (on `_driftStarted` flag), `playDriftTierUp(tier)` (on `_driftTierChanged` flag), `playBoostFire()` (on `_boostStarted` flag), `playWallHit()` (new `_wallHitFrame` flag from physics.js wall collision), and `playKartBump()` (new `_kartBumpFrame` flag from physics.js kart-kart collision). All flags are player-only to avoid audio spam from 7 AI karts. Flags are consumed (cleared) after triggering the sound.
+- Verified: pass — Zero console errors on all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak). 8/8 karts racing on all tracks. All audio functions confirmed present and callable. Shadow camera tracks player position correctly.
\ No newline at end of file
